Previous studies have demonstrated the positive effects of phytogenic feed additives such as essential oils on growth performance and digestive functions of broiler chickens (
 Jamroz et al., 2003; 
 Murugesan et al., 2015; 
 Barbarestani et al., 2020). In addition to improving immune response, such additives also enhance antioxidant capacity and meat quality in broiler chickens (
 Hashemipour et al., 2013; 
 Chowdhury et al., 2018a; 
 Shirani et al., 2019). However, some studies on the use of phytogenic feed additives in poultry nutrition have indicated inconsistent results on productive animal performance, as reported by 
 Jang et al. (2007) and 
 Chamorro et al. (2013).
